          "id": "dtcase-5d52ae0f53fa161c",
          "title": "# Case Study: Horizon Solutions\n\n## Introduction\n\nHorizon Solutions is an established leader in the global sustainable p...",
          "content": "**Comprehensive Business Strategy for Horizon Solutions**\n### Problem Statement and Recommendations\n**Core Issue:** Escalating costs of raw materials for biodegradable plastics and regulatory pressure.\n**Recommendations:**\n1. **Raw Material Sourcing Optimization:**\n\t* Collaborate with Sophia Patel and engage external auditors to audit Horizon's existing suppliers to identify more cost-effective alternatives and ensure compliance with regulatory standards.\n\t* Develop a competitive procurement process to establish strong partnerships with low-cost, environmentally responsible suppliers.\n2. **Innovation-Driven Revenue Growth:**\n\t* Engage Mark and internal innovation teams to develop new, high-margin product offerings that can be manufactured with the same, or even lower, raw materials costs.\n\t* Invest in cutting-edge bioplastics research to identify emerging technologies that can address the escalating raw material costs and regulatory challenges.\n3. **Regulatory Compliance and Risk Management:**\n\t* Work closely with Sophia to establish a proactive compliance program, ensuring continuous audits and testing to mitigate potential regulatory risks.\n\t* Develop a robust risk management framework to identify, assess, and address potential risks associated with raw material sourcing and regulatory compliance.\n### Key People to Collaborate With\n1. **Sophia Patel:** Director of Regulatory Compliance\n2. **Mark:** Sales Manager\n3. **Emily Greenfield:** Founder and CEO (to be briefed on the strategy and provide necessary guidance)\n4. **Internal Innovation Teams:** Research and development teams responsible for identifying and developing new biodegradable plastics technologies\n### Systems and Processes to Optimize\n1. **Procurement Platform:** Implement a modern procurement platform to streamline supplier identification, evaluation, and selection.\n2. **Compliance Framework:** Develop a comprehensive compliance framework that includes regular audits, testing, and reporting to...\nContext recap: **Comprehensive Business Strategy for Horizon Solutions**\n### Problem Statement and Recommendations\n**Core Issue:** Escalating costs of raw materials for biodegradable plastics and regulatory pressure. **Recommendations:**\n1. **Raw Material Sourcing Optimization:**\n\t* Collaborate with Sophia Patel and engage external auditors to audit Horizon's existing suppliers to identify more cost-effective alternatives and ensure compliance with regulatory standards. * Develop a competitive procurement process to establish strong partnerships with low-cost, environmentally responsible suppliers.\nWhy this matters: Business Case Studies — Concepts 16 helps learners in Science connect ideas from Business Case Studies (Master's Level) to decisions they make during practice and assessment. Highlight tradeoffs, assumptions, and verification.\nContext recap: **Comprehensive Business Strategy for Horizon Solutions**\n### Problem Statement and Recommendations\n**Core Issue:** Escalating costs of raw materials for biodegradable plastics and regulatory pressure. **Recommendations:**\n1. **Raw Material Sourcing Optimization:**\n\t* Collaborate with Sophia Patel and engage external auditors to audit Horizon's existing suppliers to identify more cost-effective alternatives and ensure compliance with regulatory standards. * Develop a competitive procurement process to establish strong partnerships with low-cost, environmentally responsible suppliers.\nWhy this matters: Business Case Studies — Concepts 16 helps learners in Science connect ideas from Business Case Studies (Master's Level) to decisions they make during practice and assessment. Highlight tradeoffs, assumptions, and verification.\nStep-by-step approach: (1) define the goal in one sentence, (2) identify evidence that supports the goal, (3) explain how each piece of evidence changes your conclusion, and (4) verify the final answer against the original goal and constraints.",
